{"title":"•Amoxicilina","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/General/•Amoxicilina-2024.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"• Amoxicilina","guid":"3jf2TBFadvYkMBV_hRRUuQ","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Uso y\\NDosificación","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"• Estructura:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"3","parent":"2","text":"• Amoxicilina = Ampicilina + grupo hidroxilo (-OH) → ↑ absorción oral\\N→ ↓ frecuencia de dosis: Amoxicilina 3x/día vs. Ampicilina 4x/día","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"• Formulación ER:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"5","parent":"4","text":"• Dosis diaria única para faringitis estreptocócica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"4","text":"• No triturar ni masticar","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"7","parent":"1","text":"• Preparación IV:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"8","parent":"7","text":"• Disponible en UK y Europa (no en EE.UU.)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"7","text":"• Amoxicilina IV se convierte rápidamente en Ampicilina","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"10","parent":"1","text":"• Dosis alta:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"11","parent":"10","text":"• Recomendado para otitis media y neumonía adquirida en la comunidad en niños","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"12","parent":"1","text":"Riesgo en Embarazo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"13","parent":"12","text":"• Categoría de riesgo FDA 1: Sin evidencia de toxicidad en humanos o animales","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"12","text":"• Uso durante lactancia: Concentraciones bajas en leche, no se esperan efectos adversos.\\NMonitorear toxicidad GI en el infante","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"15","parent":"1","text":"Dosis en\\NAdultos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"16","parent":"15","text":"• Dosis usual: 500-1000 mg po tid","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"15","text":"• Dosis ER: 775 mg po 1x/día (1 tab)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"15","text":"• Profilaxis post-exposición a Ántrax en embarazo: 1000 mg po q8h x 60 días","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"15","text":"• Faringotonsilitis: 500 mg po q8h o 1000 mg po qd o 775 mg ER po 1x/día x 10 días","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"15","text":"• H. pylori: Parte de terapia combinada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"15","text":"• Enfermedad de Lyme temprana: 500 mg po tid x 14-21 días","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"15","text":"• Neumonía adquirida en la comunidad (ambulatorio): 1000 mg po tid x 5 días mínimo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"15","text":"• Rinosinusitis: 500 mg po q8h o 875 mg po q12h x 5-7 días","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"15","text":"• Erisipela (leve) o Erisipeloide (cutáneo local): 500 mg po tid x 5-10 días","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"15","text":"• Cistitis no complicada por Enterococcus sp: 500 mg po q8h o 875 mg po q12h x 5 días","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"15","text":"• Bacteriuria asintomática por estreptococo del grupo B en embarazo: 500 mg po q8h o 875 mg po q12h x 4-7 días","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"27","parent":"1","text":"Dosis en\\NPediatría","guid":"","children":[{"id":"28","parent":"27","text":"• Dosis (Edad >28 días): 25-50 mg/kg/día (dividido q8h)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"27","text":"• Para AOM, neumonía: 80-100 mg/kg/día (dividido q8-12h; q12h para AOM)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"30","parent":"1","text":"Ajuste\\NRenal","guid":"","children":[{"id":"31","parent":"30","text":"• Peso corporal y depuración\\Nde creatinina (CrCl)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"32","parent":"31","text":"• CrCl <30 mL/min: No recibir dosis de 875 mg","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"33","parent":"30","text":"• CrCl >50-90: 775 mg q24h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"30","text":"• CrCl >30: Sin ajuste","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"30","text":"• CrCl 10-30: 250-500 mg q12h","guid":"","children":[{"id":"36","parent":"35","text":"• CrCl <30 mL/min o en HD: No se recomienda la tableta ER","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"37","parent":"30","text":"• CrCl <10: 250-500 mg q24h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"38","parent":"30","text":"• HD: 250-500 mg q24h (+ dosis extra AD)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"30","text":"• CAPD: 250-500 mg q12h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"30","text":"• CRRT: 250-500 mg q8-12h","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"41","parent":"1","text":"Ajuste Hepático","guid":"","children":[{"id":"42","parent":"41","text":"• Ninguno","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"43","parent":"1","text":"Efectos\\NAdversos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"44","parent":"43","text":"• Alergia: Rash común con\\Nantibióticos β-lactámicos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"45","parent":"44","text":"• Mononucleosis infecciosa (EBV): 65-100% desarrollan rash con Ampicilina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"44","text":"• Reacciones cruzadas: ↑ riesgo con cefalosporinas orales con cadena lateral R1 idéntica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"47","parent":"43","text":"• Amoxicilina ER: Reacciones alérgicas, diarrea asociada a C. difficile,\\Nprueba de glucosa urinaria falsa positiva con Clinitest","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"43","text":"• Otros efectos: Fiebre, prueba de Coombs positiva, neutropenia, eosinofilia (2%),\\Ntrombocitopenia (raro), ↑ PT/PTT, náuseas/vómitos (2%), diarrea (5%), colitis por C. difficile (raro)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"43","text":"• Cristalización en orina: Hematuria macroscópica e\\Ninsuficiencia renal por obstrucción tubular","guid":"","children":[{"id":"50","parent":"49","text":"• Otros medicamentos causantes de cristaluria:\\NCiprofloxacina, aciclovir, indinavir, vitamina C","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"51","parent":"0","text":"Espectro\\NAntimicrobiano","guid":"","children":[{"id